\f0\b\fs48 \cf0 EXPECTED OUTPUT:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 \'95 The LED glows and the buzzer produces sound for 1 second.\uc0\u8232 \'95 Both the LED and buzzer remain OFF for 2 seconds.\u8232 \'95 The process repeats continuously at fixed intervals.\u8232 \'95 The alert system provides both visual and auditory indications.\
\
\uc0\u11835 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa321\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs48 \cf0 INFERENCE:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The programmable timed alert system using Arduino was implemented successfully using an LED and buzzer. The delay-based approach generated alerts at fixed intervals but blocked the processor during execution. Interrupt-based timing methods provide higher precision, better responsiveness, and improved multitasking capability. Therefore, interrupt-based approaches are more suitable for real-time alert systems requiring accurate timing control.\
}